    "id": "m3042",
    "subject": "Maths",
    "page": 67,
    "chapter": "Rohan and Simran",
    "content": "53\nLet us do it on Ginladi!\nWhat is the total number of flowers used by Rohan and \nSimran?\nRohan brings\nSimran brings\nRohan and Simran \ntogether bring\nA. 25 + 12 = \nB. 57 + 34 = \nLet us understand this way.\n57 + 34 = \u000757 + 30 + 4 \n87 + 4 = 91\n \n \nCount ____ ahead of ____ \nC. 24 + 43 = \n \nWe can write 24 + 40 + 3 = 64 + 3 = 67"
