    "id": "m3209",
    "subject": "Maths",
    "page": 73,
    "chapter": "Let us Count Diyas",
    "content": "this on \nginladi too. \nI count 75 \nfirst and then I \nwill go 35 steps \nbackward.\nIf we have 32 diyas \nin the morning and \n12 diyas are sold \nby the evening. \nHow many diyas \nare left?\nOn taking away 12 from 32, we \nget 20.\n32 − 12 = 20\n20\n32\n40\n75"
