    "content": "65\n46\nTo give 18\n4 6\n− 1 8\n \n(opens 1 \n = 16 \n)\n16 − 8 = 8\n4 6\n− 1 8\n 2 8 \n16\n3\n4 6\n− 1 8\n 8 \n3\n16\n \nT O\n \nT O\n \nT O\nI am left with \n2 garlands and 8 \nflowers or 28 flowers \nin all.\nNow, Jyoti has 28 flowers in all. She gives 5 to her \nfriend. Help Jyoti to find out how many flowers is she \nleft with?\n2 8\n− 5"
